msgid ""
"A Domain Name System (DNS) available to Rackspace Cloud customers. "
"Interactions with Rackspace Cloud DNS occur programmatically via the "
"Rackspace Cloud DNS API as described in this Cloud DNS Developer Guide."
msgstr ""

#: ./doc/src/docbkx/common/glossary.xml714(glossterm)
msgid "Reboot"
msgstr ""

#: ./doc/src/docbkx/common/glossary.xml716(para)
msgid ""
"The reboot function allows for either a soft or hard reboot of a server. "
"With a soft reboot, the operating system is signaled to restart, which "
"allows for a graceful shutdown of all processes. A hard reboot is the "
"equivalent of power cycling the server."
msgstr ""

#: ./doc/src/docbkx/common/glossary.xml725(glossterm)
msgid "Rebuild"
msgstr ""

#: ./doc/src/docbkx/common/glossary.xml727(para)
msgid ""
"The rebuild function removes all data on the server and replaces it with the"
" specified image. Server ID and IP addresses remain the same."
msgstr ""

#: ./doc/src/docbkx/common/glossary.xml734(glossterm)
msgid "Record"
msgstr ""

#: ./doc/src/docbkx/common/glossary.xml736(para)
msgid ""
"A DNS record belongs to a particular domain and is used to specify "
"information about the domain. There are several types of DNS records. Each "
"record type contains particular information used to describe that record's "
"purpose. Examples include mail exchange (MX) records, which specify the mail"
" server for a particular domain, and name server (NS) records, which specify"
" the authoritative name servers for a domain."
msgstr ""

#: ./doc/src/docbkx/common/glossary.xml748(glossterm)
msgid "Resize"
msgstr ""

#: ./doc/src/docbkx/common/glossary.xml750(para)
msgid ""
"The resize function converts an existing server to a different flavor, in "
"essence, scaling the server up or down. The original server is saved for a "
"period of time to allow rollback if there is a problem. All resizes should "
"be tested and explicitly confirmed, at which time the original server is "
"removed. All resizes are automatically confirmed after 24 hours if they are "
"not confirmed or reverted."
msgstr ""

#: ./doc/src/docbkx/common/glossary.xml763(glossterm)
msgid "RESTful"
msgstr ""

#: ./doc/src/docbkx/common/glossary.xml765(para)
msgid ""
"A kind of web service API that uses REST, or Representational State "
"Transfer. REST is the style of architecture for hypermedia systems that is "
"used for the World Wide Web."
